IX. TO LOLLIUS

[Vesorte credas interitura, qua>

HINK not the words will perish that Ι sing, Born where the waters of Osanto roar 3 Words which, by poet’s art unknown before, Set to the lyre are echoed from its string.

Maeonian Homer holds the upper seat, But palms to Pindar we do not refuse 3 Nor to the Cean or Alcaeic muse,

Nor grave Stesichorus laudatiori meet.

Nor gay Anacreon’s songs of olden days Has age destroyed 3 the words that love inspires Outlive their utterance 3 and still live the fires AEolian Sappho kindled in her lays. 199
